ComfyUI Media Nodes
===================

This custom node pack contains small native ComfyUI video and audio tools.
Search for `sx_` in ComfyUI's add-node menu to find all included nodes.

Install
-------

1. Put this folder inside `ComfyUI/custom_nodes/`.
2. Restart ComfyUI.

Nodes
-----

`sx_concatenate_videos` appears under `Media Pack/video`.

Inputs:

- `video_1`: optional native `VIDEO` input, such as the output from ComfyUI's built-in
  `Load Video` node.
- `video_2`: optional native `VIDEO` input.
- `overlap_seconds`: seconds to remove from the start of `video_2` before
  joining. Leave it at `0` when there is no overlap.

Outputs:

- `video`: native `VIDEO` output. Connect it to ComfyUI's built-in `Save Video`
  node to write a file.

Notes
-----

The output always plays `video_1` followed by `video_2`.
If either video input is disconnected or empty, the node passes through the
other video unchanged.

The first video controls the output size and frame rate. If `video_2` has a
different resolution, it is resized to match `video_1`.

When `overlap_seconds` is greater than `0`, the node assumes the end of
`video_1` and the start of `video_2` contain the same content, so it removes
that duplicate section from the beginning of `video_2`.

`sx_video_clip_seconds` appears under `Media Pack/video`.

Inputs:

- `source_video`: native `VIDEO` input.
- `seconds`: how many seconds to keep. Positive values keep from the start of
  the video, negative values keep from the end of the video, and `0` keeps the
  whole video.

Outputs:

- `video`: native `VIDEO` output containing the selected section.
- `images`: native `IMAGE` batch containing the selected frames.

`sx_slice_audio` appears under `Media Pack/audio`.

Inputs:

- `source_audio`: native `AUDIO` input.
- `start`: where the cut should begin, in seconds.
- `duration`: how long the cut should be, in seconds. Set this to `0` to slice
  from `start` to the end of the audio.

Outputs:

- `audio`: native `AUDIO` output.

`sx_last_images` appears under `Media Pack/image`.

Inputs:

- `images`: native `IMAGE` batch.
- `count`: number of images to take from the end of the batch.

Outputs:

- `images`: the last `count` images from the input batch.

`sx_string_number_list_item` appears under `Media Pack/utils`.

Inputs:

- `index`: zero-based item index to select.
- `row_0_string` and `row_0_number` through `row_19_string` and
  `row_19_number`: separate fields for each list row.

The row string fields are multiline text areas. To keep the node compact,
only row `0` and the next available empty row are shown; filling a row's string
field reveals the next row.

Outputs:

- `string`: the selected item's string.
- `number`: the selected item's number.
